<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fluvial processes rather than fire primarily disturb stands. Fire response probably relates to the ability of the shrubs to sprout. Severe fires likely kill plants, as is noted for <i>Ephedra nevadensis </i>by Anderson (2004a), while less severe fires likely top-kill plants. While fire regime and post-fire regeneration information is lacking for these species, fires are likely stand-replacing events. Fire regimes may be variable and dependent upon the invasion of non-native species, such as <i>Brassica tournefortii, Bromus tectorum, </i>and <i>B. rubens</i>.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
